<p>given away with one's rations and if you are lucky you get one. They are not given for ability or for work done, for if they were many of those with colours approaching a rainbow on their breast would never have had any such thing there</p>
<p>We have a number of enthusiastic cricketers in our unit. They spend more time on cricket that at work.</p>
<p>A number of the wounded who have passed through the Palestine Campaign unscathed have been brought in to the C.C.S. severely wounded.</p>
<p>Aug 10th.<br/>Had a set to with Major.C. Taken up before the Col, who asked me to make an apology to him for being rude.</p>
<p>Trying to get a proper system into the O.T.</p>
<p>Very good news from the Somme Front</p>
<p>The road to the West of the C.C.S. has been put out of bounds to us. A fracas between some of our men and some Chinamen had taken place the other night and the thing being reported we were all made to suffer for the misdeeds of a few, as this road was our favourite evening walk.</p>
<p>Aug 11th.<br/>Got instructions to go on Leave to Paris with W.I. Left Blendecque at 9.36. a m.</p>
